# Data

## Source

All macroeconomic data is sourced from the **World Bank World Development Indicators (WDI)** database, accessed programmatically via the `WDI` R package.

## How to reproduce the dataset

Run `scripts/R/data_collection.R`. This will pull the panel data directly from the World Bank API and save it as `eupanel.dta` in this folder.

```r
# Requires R with the following packages:
# WDI, dplyr, tidyr, haven
source("scripts/R/data_collection.R")
```

## Why the .dta file is not included

The raw dataset is publicly available via the World Bank API and can be reproduced exactly using the R script. This keeps the repository lightweight and ensures data provenance is transparent.

